In a speech, President Biden thanked the Office of Personnel Management and recognized the hard work and dedication of federal workers. He emphasized the impact they have had on the lives of Americans, particularly during the COVID-19 pandemic. The President highlighted the importance of public service and the role of federal workers in restoring faith in democracy. He expressed gratitude for their sacrifices and called on them to continue delivering for the American people. President Biden also mentioned that he would be meeting with the parents of Austin Tice and stated that a decision on student loan debt has not been made yet.